    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug start --no-halt",
        "description": "Attach to running target without halting (DBG-003)"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "This maps to `stm32 debug start --no-halt` \u2014 DBG-003 attach-running semantics. The ELF will be autodiscovered from the project descriptor.\nThe session failed before attaching. The ST-LINK GDB server (exit code 6) is refusing to connect because the **ST-LINK firmware is out of date**:\n\n> `Error in initializing ST-LINK device. Reason: ST-LINK firmware upgrade required.`\n\n---\n\n**What happened:** gdbserver exited immediately at probe init \u2014 no GDB connection was attempted. This is the same class of issue flagged for the bench F401RE (onboard ST-Link V2J28M17 / `DEV_USB_COMM_ERR`).\n\n**Fix \u2014 upgrade the ST-LINK firmware:**\n\n1. Open **STM32CubeProgrammer** \u2192 top-right corner \u2192 **Firmware upgrade** (the ST-LINK icon).\n2. Select your probe from the list and click **Upgrade**.\n3. Once complete, re-run the attach:\n\n```\nstm32 debug start --no-halt\n```\n\nAlternatively, if you have the ST-LINK Upgrade standalone utility:\n\n```\nSTLinkUpgrade.exe        # Windows\nSTLinkUpgrade            # Linux\n```\n\nWould you like help running the upgrade via `stm32 prog` or CubeProgrammer once the firmware is updated?"
}